      "message": "[🔴 Critical Issues] Line 2019: This uses `std::views::values`, which requires C++20 ranges support. The daemon is still built in configurations that do not enable C++20, so this will break compilation there. Use a regular map iteration instead.\n```suggestion\n        for (const auto\u0026 [_, msg] : loadedHistory_.quickAccess) {\n            if (msg-\u003etype \u003d\u003d CommitType::TEXT \u0026\u0026 !msg-\u003epluginData.contains(\"bodyOverwrite\")) {\n                batch.push_back(*msg);\n            }\n        }\n```",
