      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🔴 Critical Issues] Line 2092: When `messageId` is an edition commit, this copies that edition\u0027s `bodyOverwrite` onto the original message\u0027s `pluginData`. That can make clients render the current message body using an overwrite computed for an older edition, and clearing an edition overwrite can also erase the original message overwrite. Store the overwrite only on the commit it belongs to, then signal the original with injected edition overwrite data.\n```suggestion\n            const auto originalIt \u003d loadedHistory_.quickAccess.find(editIt-\u003esecond);\n            if (originalIt \u003d\u003d loadedHistory_.quickAccess.end()) {\n                return;\n            }\n            signalMsg \u003d injectEditionOverwrites(*originalIt-\u003esecond, loadedHistory_.quickAccess);\n```",
