      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 2257: The patch emits `SwarmLoaded` before running `loadMissingBodyOverwrites()`, while the new handler documentation says transforms happen before `SwarmLoaded`. This exposes untransformed message bodies first and then sends updates, which can cause visible flicker and makes the API contract misleading. Apply the transform before emitting the loaded signal, or update the API contract if the two-phase delivery is intentional.\n```suggestion\n                    if (const auto convPtr \u003d convWeak.lock()) {\n                        convPtr-\u003eloadMissingBodyOverwrites();\n                    }\n                    emitSignal\u003clibjami::ConversationSignal::SwarmLoaded\u003e(id, accountId, conversationId, messages);\n```",
